BLUE CHEESE AND LEEK SOUP
http://www.honeyandbirch.com/leek-blue-cheese-soup/

3 large leeks
1/4 cup unsalted butter
2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
4 ounces crumbled blue cheese
2 tablespoons flour
1 tablespoon dijon mustard
1 teaspoon black pepper
6 cups chicken broth/stock
Garnish
1/2 cup diced scallions

Slice leeks thinly, width-wise. Over medium heat, melt the butter and olive
oil in a large soup pot. Saute the leeks for 10-15 minutes.
Add the blue cheese to the pot, stirring until the cheese is melted. Then add
the flour, stirring constantly until absorbed. Mix in the mustard and black
pepper.
Add the chicken broth and turn heat to high. Stir until soup comes to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve. Garnish with additional blue cheese and the diced scallions.
